<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Info Source - Sources of Federal Employee
Information (ISFE)</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>

<!-- Any HTML can be put in here for the header -->
<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/"><img BORDER=1 src="/Link4.gif"></a>
<BR>
<H1>Sources of Federal Employee Information (ISFE)</H1><H2>Description
of the Database</H2><P>This part of <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> is of
primary interest to current and former federal government employees.  It
contains descriptions of records held by the federal government on its
employees.</P>
<P>  In the printed publication there is one chapter for each
department and agency.  In the online service, the chapters are broken
down into small component parts which are easy to search, read and
print.</P>
<P>  For each department or agency, the following information is
provided in <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG>:</P>
<DL>
<DT><a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.qlsys.ca/TBS/Info_Source/iee2002.html"><STRONG>
Standard Banks:  </STRONG></A></DT>
<DD>Administrative matters which are common to most departments and
agencies, such as "Pay & Benefits" and "Training & Development" are
contained in Standard Banks. These are described in detail in a document
which is listed on the Menu.</DD>
</DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Particular Banks:</STRONG></DT>
<DD>When a department or agency has specific requirements for storing
personal information about its employees, this information is described
in the <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> record for a Particular Bank.  For
example, Agriculture Canada collects and keeps personal information on
employees who are interested in work assignments outside Canada.  This
collections of information is described in the "Human Resources
Inventory - International Assignments" bank.</DD></DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>  Central Banks:  </STRONG></DT>
<DD>These banks contain information about employees from several
departments.  They are maintained by central agencies such as the Public
Service Commission, the Treasury Board Secretariat and Supply and
Services.  For example, the Public Service Commission has a Central Bank
called "Inventory of Applicants for Management Trainee Program.</DD></DL>
<H2><a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.qlsys.ca/TBS/Info_Source/searchdoc.html"> Search
the Sources of Federal Employee Information (ISFE) database</A></H2><HR><P>
<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.qlsys.ca/TBS/Info_Source/tocenglish.html">
<IMG SRC="http://www.qlsys.ca/TBS/Info_Source/images/petite.gif"
></A>  Return to <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> Main Menu</P>


