<DT><EM><STRONG>March 6, 1995

</STRONG></EM></DT>

<DD>The <EM>Federal Regulatory Plan</EM> searchable database has now been

updated to include the 1995 Plan.  The Plan is prepared by the

<STRONG>Treasury Board Secretariat</STRONG>.  It provides brief descriptions of

all regulatory initiatives planned by the government for 1995, including new

regulations as well as amendments to existing ones.  It also includes a
progress

report on the 1994 initiatives.</DD></DL>

<DL>

<DT><EM><STRONG>October 14, 1994</STRONG></EM></DT>

<DD>The <EM>Assets Information Management</EM> databases have been added to

the

<EM>Info Source Bulletin Board</EM> (Choose item 9). These databases contain

documentation to provide a common framework for the management of
information on

materiel. The databases contain data element definitions and definitions of

materiel management terms.  Relational models are also included.</DD></DL>

<DL>

<DT><EM><STRONG>August 18, 1994</STRONG></EM></DT>

<DD>The <EM>Access to Information Volume</EM> and the <EM>Privacy and Data

Protection Volume</EM> of the <EM>Treasury Board Manual</EM> have been added to

the

<STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> Databases (Choose Item 8).  They complement

information that is currently available in the <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG>

Databases.  Other <EM>Treasury Board Manual Volumes</EM> will eventually be

added to this database.</DD></DL>

<DL>

<DT><EM><STRONG>June 13, 1994</STRONG></EM></DT>

