<HEAD>
<TITLE>Cornell Legal Research Encyclopedia
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#0000CD" vlink="#B03060"
background="http://www.law.cornell.edu:80/library/yellow1.jpg">

<!-- Any HTML can be put in here for the header -->
<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/"><img BORDER=1 src="/Link4.gif"></a>
<BR>


<center><table width=100%>
<tr align=center>
<td><img alt="Law tower" src="http://www.law.cornell.edu:80/library/newfron2.gif"></td>
<td><font size="+3"><B>Cornell Law Library</B></font><hr
width="25%"><font size="+2"><B>Cornell Legal Research
Encyclopedia</B></font></H2></td>
</tr>
</table>
</P></CENTER>
<hr><p>

The Legal Research Encyclopedia is a research tool for the 21st
century.  Recognizing the availability of legal materials in multiple
formats, the law librarians at Cornell Law Library are
creating the Legal Research Encyclopedia, a comprehensive compilation
of legal sources.  This compilation is a topical and jurisdictional
arrangement of all available formats, including print, microform,
CD-ROM, Westlaw, Lexis and the Internet and includes references as well
as direct links.<p>


<center>
<table border=3>
<tr>
<td><a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.law.cornell.edu:80/library/subjects.html"><IMG alt="Subjects" border=0
SRC="2s.gif"></A></td>
<td><a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.law.cornell.edu:80/library/states/us.html"><IMG alt="United States" border=0
SRC="2us.gif"></A></td>
</tr>
