<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Info Source - Sources of Federal Government
Information (ISFG)</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>

<!-- Any HTML can be put in here for the header -->
<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/"><img BORDER=1 src="/Link4.gif"></a>
<BR>
<H1>Info Source - Sources of Federal Government Information
(ISFG)</H1><H2>Description of the Database</H2><P>This component of
the <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> service is the largest and most
important. It is the primary source of information about federal
government departments and agencies.</P>
<P>In the printed publication there is one chapter for each department
and agency. In the online service, the chapters are broken down into
small component parts which are easy to search, read and print.</P>
<P> For each department or agency, the following information is
provided in <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG>:</P>
<DL>
<DT><STRONG>Background</STRONG></DT>
<DD>The history of the department and its general purpose.</DD>
</DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Responsibilities</STRONG></DT>
<DD>A description of the mandate and activities of the department.</DD></DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Legislation</STRONG></DT>
<DD>A list of Acts administered by the department.</DD></DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Organization</STRONG></DT>
<DD>A description of the structure of the department and its branches,
as well as all agencies, bureaus and commissions which come under the
authority of the department.</DD></DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Information Holdings</STRONG></DT>
<DD>Brief descriptions of the types of information held by the
department or agency. These include:<DL>
<DT><STRONG>Program Records:</STRONG></DT>
<DD>Descriptions of the information held about each program
administered by the department or agency. For example, Agriculture
Canada administers a Pest Control program. <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG>
provides a brief description of the information held by the department
on that program.</DD></DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Standard Program Records:</STRONG></DT>
<DD>Administrative matters which are common to most departments and
agencies, such as Personnel, Equipment, Buildings, etc., are contained
in Standard Program Records. These are described in detail in a document
which is listed on the Menu.</DD></DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Personal Information Banks:</STRONG></DT>
<DD>When the federal government stores personal information about
individuals, the <I>Privacy Act</I> requires that departments adhere to
certain  guidelines. Personal Information Banks are the records of the
information stored. For example, Agriculture Canada collects and keeps
personal information on the owners of animals infected with rabies.
<STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> contains a description of this Personal
Information Bank, which is called "Test Reports for Rabies".</DD></DL><DL>

<DT><STRONG>Classes of Personal Information:</STRONG></DT>
<DD>When general information about individuals does not fall into a
specific Personal Information Bank, it is classified in this section. An
example would be letters of general inquiry or letters of complaint sent
to a department.</DD></DL><DL>
<DT><STRONG>Manuals:</STRONG></DT>
<DD><STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> contains a list of all Manuals of
Procedures and Directives created and used by government employees in
their work. A Reading Room is provided by each department and agency for
individuals who wish to examine the Manuals. These Rooms are listed in
<STRONG>Info Source.</STRONG></DD></DL></DD></DL>
<H2><a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.qlsys.ca/TBS/Info_Source/searchdoc.html"> Search
the Sources of Federal Government Information (ISFG) database</A></H2><HR>
<P><a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.qlsys.ca/TBS/Info_Source/tocenglish.html">
<IMG SRC="http://www.qlsys.ca/TBS/Info_Source/images/petite.gif"></A>
Return to <STRONG>Info Source</STRONG> Main Menu</P>



