<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.tufts.edu/fletcher/secretariats.html">List of Treaty secretariats with known Internet servers</a><p>

<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.tufts.edu/departments/fletcher/multi/other.html">Other Collections of International Law</a><p>

<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.tufts.edu/departments/fletcher/multi/historical.html">Miscellaneous historical documents</a><p>

<h3><a name="About">About the Multilaterals Project</a></h3>
<blockquote>
The Multilaterals Project, begun in 1992, is an ongoing project at the
<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.tufts.edu/fletcher/">Fletcher School of Law & Diplomacy</a>, Tufts
University, Medford, Massachusetts to make available the texts of 
international multilateral conventions and other instruments. Although
the project was initiated to improve public access to environmental
agreements, the collection today also includes treaties in the fields of
human rights, commerce and trade, laws of war and arms control, and other
areas.  Although the vast majority of texts date from the second half of
this century, the collection also includes historical texts, from the
1648 <a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.tufts.edu/departments/fletcher/multi/texts/historical/westphalia.txt">Treaty of Westphalia</a> 
to the <a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.tufts.edu/departments/fletcher/multi/www/league-covenant.html">Covenant of 
the League of Nations</a>.<p>

Text versions of these files can also be found in the anonymous ftp site 
ftp://ftp.fletcher.tufts.edu/pub/diplomacy (formerly jade.tufts.edu), where
files are organized by a filenaming system based on the Bowman & Harris
guide, <I>Multilateral Treaties</I> (<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://www.ccc.nottingham.ac.uk/~llzweb/centres.htm">Nottingham Treaty Centre</a>). Users of
the ftp site should first consult the chronological <a href=ftp://ftp.fletcher.tufts.edu/pub/diplomacy/INDEX>INDEX</a> to obtain the file name.<p>


In addition to the ascii text and www versions included here, the 
anonymous ftp site also includes WordPerfect versions, 
in a subdirectory ftp://ftp.fletcher.tufts.edu/pub/diplomacy/word-perfect/.<p>
<hr>

<small><p align=center><I>This site is best viewed with Netscape, only
because many of the treaty texts marked up for W3 viewing take advantage
of the <a href="http://www.mcbinch.com/cgi-bin/mcbinch/nph-mcb?url=http://home.netscape.com/assist/net_sites/html_extensions.html">Netscape TYPE tags</a> for <B>ordered lists</B>.</I></p> 
  
<p align=center>Please report any problems
(or suggestions) to <a href="mailto:pstott@emerald.tufts.edu">pstott@emerald.tufts.edu</a>.</p></small>



<hr>
<small>Update: 7 February 1996</small><p>

