<head>
<title>PRELUDE PRESS & Peter McWilliams</title>
</head>

<BODY BACKGROUND="./images/marble.gif">
<div align=CENTER>
<center>
<p>
<img border=0 width=475 height=40 src="./images/pmbanr3.gif">
<p>
<img src=./images/greenhlf.gif>
</center>
</div>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<DD>Hello.
<p>
<DD>Welcome to my home page.
<p>
<DD>Here you will find the complete text of all my books currently in print, plus works "in progress." You are welcome to read, search, download, copy, print, or give away any of it. Just don't try to sell large chunks of it, or I'll call the FBI.  (See the first 30 seconds of any rental videotape.)
<p>
<DD>You're certainly free to incorporate portions of these books in what you create, and sell that. That's the nature of the creative process. There's no need to ask me to "grant permission". Who the hell am I to "grant permission"?
<p>
<DD>[If you would like to read <A HREF="philo.htm">MY PHILOSOPHY OF CREATED STUFF (AKA "ART", AKA "INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY"), please click here</A>.]
<p>

<DD>This web site is a completely free site. If, however, you should find yourself brimming with generosity, please send a donation to the Los Angeles Shanti Foundation, a non-profit organization providing education and caring to people with HIV, AIDS, and their loved ones.<p>
To donate to the Los Angeles Shanti Foundation, please contact them at:<p>

<FONT SIZE=3>1616 North La Brea Avenue<br>
Los Angeles, California  90028<br>
Telephone:  (213) 962-8197</FONT><p>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<pre>
</pre>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenline.gif">
<p>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H2>Books currently available on this site</H2>
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>

<DD>All books found at this web site are available for purchase at your local bookstore.
If you wish, you can also order any of the books directly from Prelude Press, by calling TOLL-FREE number below,
 or by using our new online order form.<p>

<table width=85%><tr><td><center><B><FONT SIZE=+3>1-800-LIFE-101</FONT><br>
<FONT SIZE=+2>(1-800-543-3101)</FONT></B></center></td>
<td><center><a href= form.htm><img src="order.gif" width=152 height=93 border=0 alt="Order Online"></a></center></td></tr></table>

<p>
<DD>Some books are available on Audio Cassettes.<br>
<DD>Most of the paperbacks are $5.95 or $6.95, which is probably less than what you'd pay for the paper to print them on.  (Some books top 600 pages).
<p>

<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">

<p>Clicking any of the titles (or any highlighted text) below will take you to the book.  From there you can:
   <UL COMPACT TYPE=disc>
<LI>Return to this page (the Home Page).<br>
<LI>Use the Book Index to go directly to any page in any book containing your search word(s).<br>
<LI>View the Table of Contents.
<LI>From the Table of Contents, you can go to any chapter.
<p></UL>
To access the Index Now, <A HREF="search.cgi">Click Here</a>
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>

<a href="http://www.hypericum.com"><img src="hyp.gif" width=150 height=169 border=0 align=left alt="Hypericum & Depression"><font size=+3>Hypericum & Depression</font></a>
<p><I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
Can Depression Be Successfully Treated with a Safe, Inexpensive, Medically Proven Herb Available without a Prescription?<br clear=all>
Hardcover 200 pages $19.95
<p>
<A HREF="./books/aint/f01.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/aintcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>

<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/aint/f01.htm">Ain't Nobody's Business If You Do</A></font><img src="./images/new001.gif"><br>
<A HREF="./books/aint/f01.htm">The Absurdity of Consensual Crimes in Our Free Country</A><p>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>This year we will spend $50 billion jailing 4 to 6 million fellow citizens for "crimes" that did not harm the person or property of another.  This makes no sense to me, and in 700 pages I explain how nonsensical (and harmful) this all is.
<p>
Paperback, 700 pages,  $9.95
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>

<A HREF="./books/life1/lf1toc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/li101cov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/life1/lf1toc.htm">LIFE 101</A></font><br>
<A HREF="./books/life1/lf1toc.htm">Everything We Wish We Had Learned About Life In SchoolBut Didn't<p></A>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>The basic handbook for life.  How's that for a pretentious statement?  Let me know what I've missed.
<p>
Paperback, 400 Pages,  $5.95
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>


<A HREF="./books/doit/doittoc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/doitcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/doit/doittoc.htm">DO IT!</A></font> <A HREF="./books/doit/doittoc.htm">Let's Get Off Our Buts<br></A>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>When faced with an exciting new opportunity, one that might expand our capabilities and move us ever-closer to living our dreams, we respond with one of two three-letter words: <B>YES</B> or <B>BUT</B>.<p>
<DD>(Yes, some have merged them into <B>YES-BUT</B>, but they really mean <B>BUT</B>.)<P>
<DD>When used in a sentence, <B>BUT</B> means, "Ignore all that good-sounding stuff that came beforehere comes the truth."  "I'm excited about my new exercise program, but..."  "I'm really concerned about the environment, but..."  "I know how important it is to love myself, but..."<p>
<DD>Getting off our buts sounds very nice, <B>BUT HOW DO WE GET OFF OUR BUTS???</B>  Simple.  Just... <font size=+2><B>DO IT!</B></font><p>
Paperback, 500 pages,  $5.95<br>


<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>


<A HREF="./books/lux/luxtoc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/luxcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/lux/luxtoc.htm">You Can't Afford The Luxury Of A Negative Thought</A></font><br>
<A HREF="./books/lux/luxtoc.htm">A Book for People with Any Life-Threatening IllnessIncluding Life<br></A>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
This is a book for anyone afflicted with one of the primary diseases of our time:  negative thinking.<p>
<p>
Paperback,  $5.95

<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>
<A HREF="./books/sur/srtoc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/srcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/sur/srtoc.htm">How to Survive the Loss of a Love</A></font><br>
<I>by</I></font> Melba Colgrove, Ph.D., Harold H. Bloomfield, M.D., & Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>The most directly helpful book on the subject of loss ever written.  Clear, simple, comforting, inspiringit gives the reader what he or she needs at each step in the process of recovering from a loss.<p>
<p>
<DD>(Please download and email to anyone in a loss situation)
<p>
200 Pages,<br>
Hardcover:  $10.00<br>
Paperback:  $5.95<br>
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>
</div>

<A HREF="./books/dep/deptoc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/depcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/dep/deptoc.htm">How to Heal Depression</A></font><br>
<I>by</I> Harold H. Bloomfield, M.D. & Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>More than two-thirds of the fifteen million Americans who are depressed don't know it.  One of them may be your friend, co-worker, child, parent, or spouse.<p>
<DD>One of them may even be you.<p>
<DD>If you think there's even a <I>possibility</I> you or someone you love <I>may</I> be depressed, please read this book.<p>
<DD>At least <I>glance</I> at the <A HREF="./books/dep/dep1a.htm#Symptoms of Depression">Symptoms of Depression</A><p>
<p>

Hardcover, 200 pages:  $14.95<br>
Audio Tapes, 6 tapes, read by the authors:  $15.95<br>
Paperback, 200 pages:  $5.95<br>

<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>


<A HREF="./books/love101/love1toc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/lovecov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/love101/love1toc.htm">LOVE 101</A></font><br>
<A HREF="./books/love101/love1toc.htm">To Love Oneself is the Beginning of a Lifelong Romance</A><br>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD><I>If you were arrested for being kind to yourself ...<p>
<DD>Would there be enough evidence to convict you?</I><p>

