<a href="http://www.hypericum.com"><img src="hyp.gif" width=150 height=169 border=0 align=left alt="Hypericum & Depression"><font size=+3>Hypericum & Depression</font></a>
<p><I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
Can Depression Be Successfully Treated with a Safe, Inexpensive, Medically Proven Herb Available without a Prescription?<br clear=all>
Hardcover 200 pages $19.95
<p>
<A HREF="./books/aint/f01.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/aintcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>

<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/aint/f01.htm">Ain't Nobody's Business If You Do</A></font><img src="./images/new001.gif"><br>
<A HREF="./books/aint/f01.htm">The Absurdity of Consensual Crimes in Our Free Country</A><p>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>This year we will spend $50 billion jailing 4 to 6 million fellow citizens for "crimes" that did not harm the person or property of another.  This makes no sense to me, and in 700 pages I explain how nonsensical (and harmful) this all is.
<p>
Paperback, 700 pages,  $9.95
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>

<A HREF="./books/life1/lf1toc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/li101cov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/life1/lf1toc.htm">LIFE 101</A></font><br>
<A HREF="./books/life1/lf1toc.htm">Everything We Wish We Had Learned About Life In SchoolBut Didn't<p></A>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>The basic handbook for life.  How's that for a pretentious statement?  Let me know what I've missed.
<p>
Paperback, 400 Pages,  $5.95
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>


<A HREF="./books/doit/doittoc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/doitcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/doit/doittoc.htm">DO IT!</A></font> <A HREF="./books/doit/doittoc.htm">Let's Get Off Our Buts<br></A>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
<DD>When faced with an exciting new opportunity, one that might expand our capabilities and move us ever-closer to living our dreams, we respond with one of two three-letter words: <B>YES</B> or <B>BUT</B>.<p>
<DD>(Yes, some have merged them into <B>YES-BUT</B>, but they really mean <B>BUT</B>.)<P>
<DD>When used in a sentence, <B>BUT</B> means, "Ignore all that good-sounding stuff that came beforehere comes the truth."  "I'm excited about my new exercise program, but..."  "I'm really concerned about the environment, but..."  "I know how important it is to love myself, but..."<p>
<DD>Getting off our buts sounds very nice, <B>BUT HOW DO WE GET OFF OUR BUTS???</B>  Simple.  Just... <font size=+2><B>DO IT!</B></font><p>
Paperback, 500 pages,  $5.95<br>


<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
<p>


<A HREF="./books/lux/luxtoc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/luxcov.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/lux/luxtoc.htm">You Can't Afford The Luxury Of A Negative Thought</A></font><br>
<A HREF="./books/lux/luxtoc.htm">A Book for People with Any Life-Threatening IllnessIncluding Life<br></A>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>
This is a book for anyone afflicted with one of the primary diseases of our time:  negative thinking.<p>
<p>
Paperback,  $5.95

<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif">
