<A HREF="./books/quotes/qt_toc.htm"><IMG SRC="./images/quotes.gif" width=100 height=160 border=1 align=LEFT hspace=15 vspace=5></A>
<pre>
</pre>
<font size=+3><A HREF="./books/quotes/qt_toc.htm">The LIFE 101 Book of Quotes</A></font><br>
<I>by</I> Peter McWilliams<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenhlf.gif"><p>

<DD>All the quotes (that is, the stuff other people wrote) from the books in The LIFE 101 Series:
<ul>
<LI>You Can't Afford the Luxury of a Negative Thought
<LI>How to Survive the Loss of a Love
<LI>LOVE 101 
<LI>LIFE 101 
<LI>DO IT! Let's Get Off Our Buts 
</ul>
<DD>All the parts that I wrotethe boring bitshave been whacked away by a team of machete-wielding Library Science majors. What's left I acknowledge as the best (he said, proud of his humility). <br>


<p>
<p>
Hardcover, 2,700 quotes, 400 pages:  $24.95<br>
Special:  $11.95

<center>
<div align=center>
<p>
<IMG SRC="./images/greenline.gif"><p>

That's about it. Have a good time.
<p>
I close with the following from the philosopher SENECA:
<p>
<I>"The fates lead those who will - those who won't, they drag."</I>

<p><A HREF="mailto:peter@mcwilliams.com">Peter McWilliams</A>
<br>To contact me by e-mail, please click on my name.
<p>

<IMG SRC="./images/greenline.gif">
